1	//! Shared harness for CLI subprocess integration tests.
2	//!
3	//! Lives under `tests/common/` so Cargo treats it as a shared module
4	//! (a top-level `tests/common.rs` would be compiled as its own test
5	//! crate). Each `tests/<name>.rs` declares `mod common;` to opt in.
6	//!
7	//! Cargo compiles each `tests/*.rs` as its own crate; helpers used
8	//! by some test crates but not others get dead-code warnings in the
9	//! crates that don't reach them. The crate-level allow below mutes
10	//! that — it's the standard idiom for shared `tests/common/`.
11	//!
12	//! - `vc_x1()` returns a `Command` for the binary Cargo built for
13	//!   the current test crate, resolved via the
14	//!   `CARGO_BIN_EXE_<bin-name>` env var with the name derived
15	//!   from `CARGO_PKG_NAME` — rename-proof, see Cargo.toml.
16	//! - `run_ok` / `run_err` wrap `Command::output` with a panic on
17	//!   the unexpected exit status, embedding stdout/stderr in the
18	//!   message so failures are debuggable.
19	//! - `CliFixture` owns a per-test tempdir under `$TMPDIR` and
20	//!   removes it on drop. Subprocesses get `HOME` overridden to a
21	//!   tempdir-scoped path so user config can't leak into or out of
22	//!   the test.
23	
24	#![allow(dead_code)]
25	
26	use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};
